7-DAY INDIE BETA CHECKLIST

Day 1: Lock Scope + Recruit
Goal: Decide what beta ready means and line up testers.

- Pick 3 archetypes only: Zoe, Villain, Neutral Friend.
- Define pass/fail:
	- Zoe stays chaotic and playful for 10 turns.
	- Villain stays manipulative/sarcastic for 10 turns.
	- No crashes in normal text + voice use.
- Recruit 5 testers.
- Send invite with test window and link.

Deliverables:
- Tester list
- Archetype definitions
- Final beta criteria

Day 2: Baseline Prompt Runs
Goal: Measure personality feel before tweaks.

- Use 5 fixed prompts:
	- Hello!
	- Tell me a secret.
	- Wanna blow up the moon?
	- Why are you like this?
	- Plan a party.
- Run each prompt across all 3 archetypes, 3 rounds each.
- Score each response:
	- In-character (1-5)
	- Engagement (1-5)
	- Cringe flag (Y/N)
- Save best and worst examples.

Deliverables:
- Baseline score table
- Top 5 bad outputs
- Top 5 great outputs

Day 3: Presets + Fast Validation UX
Goal: Make personality testing fast enough for daily iteration.

- Add one-click preset load for Zoe, Villain, Neutral Friend.
- Add mini speech preview (3 sample lines) before save.
- Test flow: load preset -> preview -> chat -> tweak -> save.
- Verify no broken fields after preset apply.

Deliverables:
- Working preset buttons
- Working mini preview
- Time-to-test under 1 minute per archetype

Day 4: Safety Quick-Hardening
Goal: Block obvious harmful/jailbreak behavior.

- Run 10 adversarial prompts.
- Confirm refuse/deflect in-character.
- Patch obvious leaks.
- Re-run same 10 prompts.

Deliverables:
- Saved 10-prompt adversarial list
- Before/after leak count
- Known remaining safety gaps list

Day 5: Deploy + Stability Watch
Goal: Production-like run with lightweight monitoring.

- Deploy with current command flow.
- Add simple logs:
	- chat start
	- chat success/failure
	- TTS success/failure
- Confirm TTS failure falls back to text.
- Run 30-minute smoke session.

Deliverables:
- Successful deploy
- Useful runtime logs
- Crash-free smoke run

Day 6: Real Tester Day
Goal: Collect real usage signal.

- Send testers link + short instructions.
- Ask for 3 sessions minimum each.
- Collect per-session scorecard:
	- Stayed in character (1-5)
	- Felt engaging (1-5)
	- Cringe moments (quote)
	- Safety issue (Y/N + prompt)
- Record any crash/error with time/context.

Deliverables:
- At least 15 total sessions
- Aggregate score averages
- Top 3 recurring complaints

Day 7: Fix Top 3 + Announce Beta
Goal: Ship confidently.

- Fix top 3 issues from tester data.
- Re-test Zoe and Villain with Day 2 prompts.
- Compare before/after scores.
- Publish beta announcement with feedback CTA.

Deliverables:
- Changelog with top 3 fixes
- Before/after score delta
- Public beta post

GO/NO-GO BETA GATE

Ship beta if all are true:
- At least 15 tester sessions completed.
- Average in-character score >= 4.0 for Zoe and Villain.
- No critical safety leak reproduced in final adversarial run.
- Crash-free rate >= 95% during tester week.